Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: django-paginated
Version: 0.1.3
Summary: Simple django digg-style pagination.
Home-page: http://github.com/simas/django-paginated
Author: Simas Skrebi≈°kis
Author-email: simas.skrebiskis@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: django-paginated
        ================
        
        Installation
        ------------
        
        ```
        pip install django-paginated
        ```
        
        and add `paginated` to project's `INSTALLED_APPS`
        
        
        Example
        -------
        
        To add pagination just change from:
        
        ```python
        def events(request):
            events = Event.objects.all()
        
            context = {
                'events': events,
            }
            return render_to_response(request, 'events.html', context)
        ```
        
        to
        
        ```python
        def events(request):
            events, pagination = paginated(Event.objects.all(), request)
        
            context = {
                'events': events,
                'pagination': pagination,
            }
            return render_to_response(request, 'events.html', context)
        ```
        
        
        and in template add line:
        
        ```
        {{ pagination|safe }}
        ```
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
